Jenkins : 

Jenkins is deployed based on Java Langauage 
we can automate teh build and deployment process 

Pre-reqrusiste 

1. Java should be installed in your machine
2. Jenkins Will run default port 8080 

How to install the jenkins: 
1. Lanuch a EC2 instance 

2. Add this repo 
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo \
    https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
3. import the key  

    sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

4. sudo yum upgrade 
5. sudo yum install jenkins 

To install java use 
sudo yum install java-21-amazon-corretto -y
cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword

Pipeline Sciprt -- 

Declearatvie 
Scripted 

Jenkins will works on Master and slave concepts 

MAster ---> Multiple slave 


By deafualt all the Jenkins inforamtion is stored in the below path 
/var/lib/jenkins

config.xml -- Global config 
credentials  -- To save password and secrets 
plugins --> to intergate with diffrent tools 
Jobs : ( Pre defined jobs or Adhoc Task )
    Config.xml -- Jobs (xml)
    builds: How many builds (files)
    workspace -Logical namespace 
nodes: Workload 

Jobs -- Task 

1 Freestyle jobs  basic Scripts --> complex 
2. Pipeline Stages -----< Jenkinsfile >
3. Multibarnach --- env (main,uat,qa )
4. Multiconfig -- Java 13 17 23 ,  
5. folder -- Grouping of jobs (uat - 5 )


